fields.physical_description:
Oak inlaid with decoration. The head decorated with a row of three arcades within sunken gadrooned panels alternating with a row of three arcades with grotesque herms, all carved in relief. The arcades filled with architectural and floral motives in marquetry and similarly inscribed with marriage initials 'TB' and 'MB' flanking the date 1590.
Above the arcades a frieze of compressed wood shavings and a dentated cornice. On the underside, four rectangular sunken corner panels and a central panel. 
Posts in the form of baluster columns, reeved above, and fluted below, on square plinths. Bedstack joined to the headboard and, at the foot, to square supports, the horizontal beams grooved.
Most of the upper moulding and the dented cornice of the tester renewed on both sides.
fields.dimensions: Height: 45.7 cm, Length: 238.8 cm, Width: 175.3 cm
